# ===========================================================================
# .gitignore for code_insights/  (Mecanum PINN digital twin)
# Goal: keep source + configs + notebooks + CSV data products + checkpoints.
# Exclude heavy binary solver references, regenerable figures, caches, scratch.
# ===========================================================================

# --- Heavy binary solver references (983 MB; reproducible) ---------------
# The .jld2 reference TRAJECTORIES for the solver-ablation / work-precision
# study have been MOVED OUT of the repo to ../data/solver_ablation_studies/
# (dense 39-D state at tol 1e-10..1e-12, ~73 MB each; the notebook now writes
# them there via REF_DIR). The benchmark folder keeps only its small
# conclusions (SOLVER_SELECTION.md, stage*_results.arrow, executed notebooks).
# This rule is defensive in case any .jld2 is regenerated inside the repo.
*.jld2

# --- Images: regenerated from CSV diagnostics ----------------------------
# (You build figures from the CSVs, so they don't belong in git.)
# NOTE: if the slide deck needs a static asset (e.g. VNIT logo), force-add it
#       with:  git add -f presentation/<logo>.png
*.png
*.svg
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif

# --- Python caches / compiled -------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Scratch / temp (per CLAUDE.md conventions) --------------------------
_tmp/
_nb_read_eval/
.headroom/
kimi_start_prompt.txt

# --- Logs, DBs, process output ------------------------------------------
*.log
*.out
*.db

# --- Environments (don't sync venvs across Win <-> WSL2) -----------------
.venv/
venv/
env/
myenv/

# --- OS / editor junk ----------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~
*.swp
.vscode/
.idea/

# ===========================================================================
# Explicitly KEPT (documented so future-you doesn't second-guess):
#   *.csv     diagnostic data products (figures rebuild from these)
#   *.ipynb   notebooks  (consider stripping outputs before commit; see below)
#   *.pdf     decks / reference papers
#   *.html    rendered trajectory diagnostics
#   *.pt *.pth *.npz   trained checkpoints + decimated caches
#   *.toml *.jl *.py *.md *.tex *.arrow(fixtures)
# ===========================================================================
